# DEBUG overlay fragment — merged ON TOP of tutorial.config to build a SEPARATE
# kernel for Module D's D1 (lockdep) and D2 (KCSAN) lessons
# (harness/build-debug-kernel.sh). It is NEVER merged into the base tutorial
# kernel: lock-dependency proving and the concurrency sanitizer slow every boot,
# so in real life you build a dedicated debug kernel to chase a deadlock or a
# data race — which is exactly what this overlay models.
#
# PROVE_LOCKING = lockdep: records every lock acquisition ORDER and reports a
# "possible circular locking dependency" the first time it sees a cycle — no
# actual deadlock needed.
CONFIG_DEBUG_KERNEL=y
CONFIG_PROVE_LOCKING=y
# KCSAN = the Kernel Concurrency Sanitizer: the compiler instruments plain memory
# accesses; watchpoints catch two CPUs touching the same address with no ordering.
CONFIG_KCSAN=y
# Stack traces in both report shapes.
CONFIG_STACKTRACE=y
